    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ransom</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Sept. 27.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 69.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit the inclosed copies
                    of a letter from Secretary Mariscal, requesting me to act as arbitrator in the
                    designated convention between Mexico and Guatemala. Copies of a similar, letter
                    from the Guatemalan minister, Mr. Emilio de Leon, have already been sent to your
                    Department.</p>
                <p>I have not felt at liberty to accept this trust without your approbation. I see
                    no chance for any unpleasant complication in anyway with our Government. I
                    should like an answer by telegraph.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. W. Ransom.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 69.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mariscal</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Ransom</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-18">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Minister</hi>: In compliance with Article II of the
                        convention had on the 1st of April of the current year, between the
                        representatives of the Governments of Mexico and Guatemala, at my proposal
                        your excellency has been designated to act in the arbitration provided for
                        in said article.</p>
                    <p>I hope that your excellency will be pleased to accept said appointment as a
                        token of friendly deference toward both Governments; and it gratifies me to
                        reiterate the assurance of my highest regard.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Igno. Mariscal.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
